    { q: "What is the primary function of the Windows 'Clipboard'?", options: ["To hold deleted files", "To serve as a temporary RAM buffer for data that has been Cut or Copied", "To organize folders", "To format hard drives"], ans: 1, exp: "The clipboard holds your copied text or images until you paste them or overwrite them with a new copy." }
