    { q: "What does 'S.M.A.R.T.' monitor on a hard drive?", options: ["It formats the drive automatically", "It monitors internal physical attributes (like read errors, spin-up time, and temperature) to mathematically predict and warn of an impending hardware failure", "It encrypts stored data", "It boosts the RPM of the drive"], ans: 1, exp: "Self-Monitoring, Analysis, and Reporting Technology helps prevent catastrophic data loss by giving users time to back up failing drives." }
